Anonymous Tue 01 Aug 2023 06:22:13 No.58458978 Report
Quoted By: >>58459046
>>58458683
Very well!

After avoiding confrontation, that sort of "I'll ignore you if you ignore me" in the workplace, they are sent off together to a "team-building convention".
Several tense moments are had with her usually being the more aggressive. She's a go-getting type where he's the type to lean back and strategize usually. She flounders under intense pressure where he maneuvers deftly in any situation.
Finally he asks "why do you hate me?" She's taken aback but can't help but laugh, the absurdity of hating someone over a dream. She vaguely explains and apologizes...until he bluntly explains their shared dreams. Their past lives.
Her attempt at decorum shattered, she fills in gaps when she can, horrified at the realization.
Now put on the spot together, they set on asking "why?" And "can we fix this?"
He feels a flood of relief, they quickly grow so much closer. Throughout this, they hadn't realized they had begun to get snowed into their hotel, trapping them together. Their shared love comes bubbling back, the ease they feel together overwhelming.
Finally, she can't take it anymore and jumps his bones, which turns into wild and frantic love-making (rather vicious at that). Late the next day, the snow stops.
The fox remembers a nickname for an orgasm "le'petit morte" the little death. (Cheesy I know, but it's what I had) The two laugh hoping maybe they avoided their fate with every little death.

When they attempt to leave the parking lot the next day, they are pushed off a ravine by a snowplow, their fates ambiguous.

It was a rather self-indulgent, "spur of the moment" inspiration, but I had planned more dreams and fights through the ages.
